        "_account_id": 130,
        "name": "Nikitas Angelinas",
        "email": "nikitas.angelinas@hpe.com",
        "username": "nikitas_angelinas"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-05 21:48:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\ni added some Doxygen comments, please let me know if you think more should be added, i just didn't want to add too many.\n\nJames, Liang, since NRS policy instances run over a single CPT, i think we can pass the CPT id as well as the CPT table that Liang mentioned during heap creation, and then just dereference these all the way down to CBH_ALLOC like James has done.\n\nBtw, it may be debateable which of 'having NRS policies run over a specific CPT' vs 'having them run over all service CPTs' may be best; i think the former is cleaner but should result in each CPT messing each other's request ordering streams, the latter will guarantee uniform ordering but would probably need some inter-CPT locking (i.e. as in pre-SMP scaling ptlrpc_service) but that is probably not a viable solution; i did some relevant tests which i showed at teh LAD workshop, please take a look at the slides on teh Jira ticket; any thoughts more than welcome.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
